  <h1>LG Dryer Flow Sense Error Repair Services Los Angeles County</h1>
  <p>An LG dryer flow sense error almost always comes down to one of three things: a blocked external vent, lint built up in the internal ductwork, or a failing flow sense sensor. Our LG Dryer Repair techs check external vent airflow first, since a clogged vent is the most common cause — call (323) 990-7550 for same-day diagnosis.</p>
  <p>When your LG dryer displays the flow sense error, it means the airflow system is compromised, leaving clothes damp and extending dry times. Our technicians diagnose and repair flow sense errors across Beverly Hills, Pasadena, and all of LA County - call (323) 990-7550 for same-day service.</p>

<h2>Signs Your LG Dryer Flow Sense Error Needs Professional Repair</h2>
<p>Across our LG Dryer Repair calls in LA, Orange, and Ventura County, flow sense errors follow a predictable pattern: a blocked external vent is by far the most common cause, followed by lint built up in the internal ductwork, with a failing flow sense sensor making up a smaller share.</p>
<p>The flow sense error typically displays as d80, d90, or d95 codes on your LG dryer's display panel.</p>
