       width="600" height="600" loading="lazy" />
  <figcaption>d80 on the display means 80% airflow restriction —
  d90 and d95 mean you're close to complete blockage</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>Nine times out of ten, we see these symptoms together: clothes taking 2-3 cycles to dry completely, the dryer running longer than normal but producing lukewarm air, and lint accumulating faster than usual around the door seal. In Torrance and Glendale homes, we've noticed that dryers installed in interior laundry rooms show flow sense errors more frequently due to longer vent runs. The error occurs when your dryer's moisture sensor detects inadequate airflow, which can stem from blocked external vents, damaged ductwork, or a failing flow sense sensor itself.</p>
