  common cause of d80 and d90 codes we find on service calls</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>What makes this particularly problematic is that continuing to run the dryer with restricted airflow puts enormous strain on the heating element and can trigger secondary failures like <a href="/repairs/lg-dryer-thermal-fuse-replacement/">LG dryer thermal fuse replacement</a>. Our technicians recommend calling immediately when you see the flow sense error code - waiting often leads to more expensive repairs down the line.</p>
<h2>Our Professional Flow Sense Error Diagnostic Process</h2>
<p>When you call (323) 990-7550, our technician arrives with specialized airflow measurement tools and a complete parts inventory for same-day repairs. The first thing we check is external vent airflow using a calibrated anemometer - this tells us immediately if the blockage is internal or external to your dryer. We then disconnect the dryer and inspect the internal ductwork pathway, checking for lint buildup that standard cleaning can't reach. The flow sense sensor itself gets tested with multimeter readings to verify it's sending accurate signals to the control board.</p>
